              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The deuteron beam current of 300 mA and beam",
                "energy of 2.0 MeV. The solid Tritium-Ti target had a",
                "thickness of approximately 1.20 mg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "49-IN-115",
                "field_identifier": "NAT",
                "value": 0.957
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 115In samples were pure",
                "indium with a purity of higher than 99.99%. Disks of",
                "pure indium, 0.5 mm in thickness and 10 mm in",
                "diameter, were sandwiched between two Au foils of 0.3",
                "mm in thickness. These foils were wrapped with 0.3 mm",
                "in thickness cadmium box and put into 90 deg angle",
                "relative to the deuteron beam direction. Samples at",
                "the high energy neutron emitting direction between 0",
                "deg and 60 deg, were not sandwiched between the Au",
                "foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Well-calibrated coaxial high-purity germanium",
                "detector (GEM30P4-76, ORTEC, USA), with an entrance",
                "window thickness of 1.5 mm, a sensitive volume of 75",
                "cm3 and a sensitive diameter of 60 mm. The detector",
                "has 20% relative efficiency and an energy resolution",
                "of 1.85 keV FWHM at 1.33 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 8-h of irradiation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Corrections were made for the multiple scattering (S)",
                "and the flux attenuation (F). The total correction",
                "factor was calculated by F = S x D. For 2.95 MeV,",
                "3.94 MeV and 5.24 MeV, S were 1.013, 0.977 and 1.016,",
                "D were 0.960, 0.970 and 0.966, F were 0.973, 0.948",
                "and 0.981."
              ]
            }
          ],
